# ServiceNow IT Support Reports and Performance Dashboard

## Project Overview

I built a ServiceNow reports and dashboard project using the Incident table.

The dashboard helps IT Support and Service Desk teams monitor incident workload, priority, state, assignment group workload, monthly trends, and high priority active incidents.

## Tools Used

- ServiceNow Personal Developer Instance
- ServiceNow Reports
- ServiceNow Dashboards
- Incident Table
- Filters and Conditions
- Data Visualizations

## Reports Created

### 1. Open Incidents by Priority

Shows active incidents grouped by priority.

- Table: Incident [incident]
- Filter: Active is true
- Group by: Priority
- Visualization: Bar chart

![Open Incidents by Priority](02-report-open-incidents-by-priority.png)

### 2. Incidents by State

Shows active incidents grouped by state.

- Filter: Active is true
- Group by: State
- Visualization: Donut chart

![Incidents by State](03-report-incidents-by-state.png)

### 3. Incidents by Assignment Group

Shows active incidents grouped by assignment group.

- Filter: Active is true
- Group by: Assignment group
- Visualization: Bar chart

![Incidents by Assignment Group](04-report-incidents-by-assignment-group.png)

### 4. Incidents Created Over Time

Shows incident creation trends over the last 12 months.

- Filter: Created on Last 12 months
- Trend by: Created
- Period: Month
- Visualization: Line chart

![Incidents Created Over Time](05-report-incidents-created-over-time.png)

### 5. High Priority Active Incidents

Shows active Critical and High priority incidents.

- Filter: Active is true AND Priority is one of 1 - Critical, 2 - High
- Visualization: List

![High Priority Active Incidents](06-report-high-priority-active-incidents.png)

## Final Dashboard

The final dashboard brings all reports together in one IT Support performance view.

